1. Nf3 d5 2. e4 {Reputedly Tennison, a lifelong e4 player, had thought for a 
while here and then said 'Better late than never!'.} dxe4 3. Ng5 f5 $4 {Yuck} 4. 
Bc4 Nh6 5. Nxh7 Rxh7 6. Qh5+ (6. Qh5+ 6... g6 7. Qxg6+) Kd7 7. Qg6 Rh8 8. Be6+ 
Kc6 9. Bxc8+ Qd6 10. Qe8+ Kb6 11. Qa4 {1-0, although after} (11. Qa4 11... Nc6) 
{it's objectively only -1 or so} 1-0

