1. e4 d5 2. Nf3 dxe4 3. Ng5 Nf6 {This is what Black should avoid and it 
demonstrates well why he should play 3...Bf5 instead.} 4. Bc4 $1 {[%cal 
Rc4f7,Rg5f7] There's a double attack on f7 and Black is forced to respond to 
this with...} e6 {...shutting in his own light-squared bishop.} *

[Event "Taming the Tennison Gambit"]
