[SourceTitle "02 Main Response: 3...Bf5"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "taming-the-tennison-gambit/course/21779, variation/2880246"]

1. e4 d5 2. Nf3 dxe4 3. Ng5 Bf5 4. Nc3 {The most commonly played move. If} (4. 
d3 exd3) {and Black is better If} (4. Bc4 e6 $1) {and Black is also better. A 
more interesting option which we'll look at is} (4. g4 $5 Bg6) Nf6 {Here White 
has the option between:} (Nf6 5. Bc4) {which we'll take as the main line} (Nf6 
5. Qe2 Nc6 $1 6. Qb5 Qd7) (Nf6 5. f3 exf3 6. Qxf3 e6 7. Bc4 Bg6 8. Qxb7 Nbd7) 
{and Black is doing well and the objectively best, but pointless} (Nf6 5. d3 
exd3 6. Bxd3 Bxd3 7. cxd3 e6) {or the equally dubious} (Nf6 5. d3 exd3 6. Qf3 e6 
7. Qxb7 Nbd7 8. Bxd3 Bxd3 9. cxd3 Rb8) 5. Bc4 e6 {Closing the diagonal.} 6. Qe2 
(6. f3) {transposes to a previous line.} Qd4 {Here we can bring the Queen to 
help. Also fine is} (6... Nc6) 7. f3 exf3 8. Nxf3 Qb6 {Or} (8... Qd8) 9. d3 Nc6 
{Black keeps his -1 and is in no danger.} *

