1. e4 d5 2. Nf3 dxe4 3. Ng5 Bf5 4. Nc3 {The best move} Nf6 {Here White has the 
option between Bc4, Qe2, f3, and (the objectively best, but pointless) d3.} 5. 
d3 {Objectively perhaps best, but practically pointless, granting Black a safe, 
hassle-free positional advantage.} exd3 6. Bxd3 Bxd3 7. cxd3 e6 {Closing the 
diagonal after which Black's a pawn up and White's d-pawn is isolated and weak. 
Also fine is} (7... h6) {Not so good is} (7... Nc6 8. Qb3) {which hits both b7 
and f7} *

