1. e4 d5 2. Nf3 dxe4 3. Ng5 Bf5 4. Nc3 {The best move} Nf6 {Here White has the 
option between Bc4, Qe2, f3, and (the objectively best, but pointless) d3.} 5. 
d3 exd3 6. Qf3 {[%cal Rf3f5,Rf3b7] A more aggressive try.} e6 7. Qxb7 Nbd7 8. 
Bxd3 Bxd3 9. cxd3 Rb8 {Here White really shouldn't take the a-pawn. However, if 
he does...} 10. Qxa7 Nc5 {[%cal Rc5b7,Rc5d3][%csl Rb7] Blocking the diagonal, 
controlling b7 and thereby threatening to trap the Queen with Ra8!} 11. Qa5 
Nxd3+ 12. Kf1 Bc5 {[%cal Rc5f2,Rd3f2] Attacking f2. This is even better than Bb4 
given by psilohead in his Scandi Supplemental repertoire.} *

