1. e4 d5 2. Nf3 dxe4 3. Ng5 Bf5 4. Nc3 {The best move} Nf6 {Here White has the 
option between Bc4, Qe2, f3, and (the objectively best, but pointless) d3.} 5. 
f3 {Keres's move, even though he reached it from} (5. Bc4 e6 6. f3) exf3 6. Qxf3 
{[%cal Rf3b7,Rf3f5]} e6 {Protect the bishop} 7. Bc4 {Angling for the Keres 
trick. If} (7. Qxb7 Nbd7) {and Black is doing well} Bg6 $1 {The only move you 
need to remember. Bauer gives} (7... Nc6 8. Nxf7 Qd4 9. Nxh8 Qxc4) 8. Qxb7 {What 
else? If} (8. d3 c6) {and Black is safe} Nbd7 9. d3 (9. d3 9... Bd6) (9. d3 9... 
Bc5) (9. d3 9... Rb8) {and} (9. d3 9... h6) {are all around -1 to -1,5 so it's 
mostly a matter of taste.} Rb8 {Play could continue} (Rb8 10. Qxa7 Bc5 11. Qa5 
O-O 12. Bd2 Ng4 $1) {and Black has a strong attack.} *

