1. e4 d5 2. Nf3 dxe4 3. Ng5 Bf5 4. Nc3 {The best move} Nf6 {Here White has the 
option between Bc4, Qe2, f3, and (the objectively best, but pointless) d3.} 5. 
Qe2 {White's Option 2} Nc6 $1 {The important move.} 6. Ngxe4 {Another way to try 
to recapture the pawn. We meet it the same way...} Nd4 $1 {[%cal Rd4e2,Rd4c2]} 
7. Qd3 {If} (7. Nxf6+ gxf6 8. Qc4 Nxc2+ 9. Kd1 c6) {and Black is winning.} e5 
{Securing the knight. Black can continue with Bc5 or moves like Nd7 or Bg6. John 
Bartholomew gives} (7... a6) {with the idea of b4-b5 next which is also fine.} *

