1. e4 d5 2. Nf3 dxe4 3. Ng5 Bf5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. Qe2 Nc6 $1 6. Qb5 {[%cal 
Rb5b7,Rb5f5] Forking the bishop and the b-pawn.} Qd7 {Defending the bishop and 
clearing the first rank. Black is doing well here and will play h6 soon. One 
possible continuation} 7. Bc4 e6 {Also ok is} (7... Bg6) {.} 8. Nxf7 {White goes 
for the typical tactic. It's important to react correctly.} Kxf7 9. Qxf5 Nd4 $1 
{[%cal Rd4f5,Rd4c2] Black will get his material back with interest.} *

