1. e4 d5 2. Nf3 dxe4 3. Ng5 e5 {This line leads to an easy advantage. There's 
probably less to learn than in the case of 3...Bf5.} 4. Nxe4 f5 5. Ng3 Nc6 {Also 
fine is preventing White's most active bishop development, Bc4, with} (5... Be6) 
6. Bb5 {White's Bc4 can be met by Qh4, attacking it laterally} (6. Bc4 Qh4 $1) 
Ne7 7. O-O {Stockfish thinks that White's strongest is} (7. d4 Qxd4 8. Qxd4 
exd4) {, but I don't see any human voluntarily going for this. Black is still 
better after that, of course.} a6 8. Bc4 {If} (8. Ba4 Qd6) {or} (8. Ba4 Be6) Qd6 
{Another approach is} (8... h5) 9. d3 f4 10. Ne2 Qg6 {Black is clearly in the 
driver's seat with the immediate threat of Bh3.} *

