[SourceTitle "03 Easy Advantage: 3...e5"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "taming-the-tennison-gambit/course/21779, variation/2880181"]

1. e4 d5 2. Nf3 dxe4 3. Ng5 e5 4. h4 {Aiming to keep the knight there.} h6 {We 
simply kick it.} 5. Nxe4 Be6 {Preventing White's, most active bishop 
development, Bc4} 6. Nbc3 Nc6 7. Bb5 Qd7 {Stepping voluntarily into the pin to 
defend the knight.} 8. Qh5 {White's best move, hitting the e-pawn laterally. If} 
(8. Bxc6 Qxc6) {If something natural like} (8. d3 O-O-O) {or} (8. d3 f5) O-O-O 
{Sacrificing the pawn for a lead in development.} 9. Bxc6 Qxc6 10. Qxe5 f5 11. 
Ng3 Nf6 12. O-O {If White gets greedy with} (12. Nxf5 Ng4 $1 13. Qe4 Qxe4 15. 
Nxe4 Bxf5) {and Black is winning} Ng4 {Or} (12... Bc5) {Who's got the initiative 
now?} *

